Many forams present but highly silicified and embedded in matrix and highly deformed. Deformation (presumably due to compaction) made identification very difficult. The genera Neogloboquadrina, Globorotalia (keeled forms) and Globigerinoides were identifiable but species were difficult. Keeled forms = 4-8 chambers, some with convex umb sides. Perhaps some are squashed G. conomiozea. Some G. plesiotumida? Perhaps some menardii but hard to say with confidence. Many many O. universa (often as compressed discs).

Comment (general): Forams present but silicified (moulds and replaced tests) and deformed. Hard to identify many forms beyond genus level. Genera present include Globorotalia (Globoconella, Menardella, Globorotalia), Neogloboquadrina, Globoturborotalita, Sphaeroidinellopsis, Globigerinoides, Globigerina. Perhaps G. praemenardii present.
